# RTL Logical Classes

Use logical utilities instead of physical ones so layout adapts to text direction (LTR/RTL). See [content/docs/(root)/rtl.mdx](content/docs/(root)/rtl.mdx).

## Positioning

Prefer logical positioning utilities so elements align correctly in both LTR and RTL:

| Physical | Logical |
| -------- | ------- |
| `left-*` | `start-*` |
| `right-*` | `end-*` |

**Exception:** Keep `left-1/2` and `-translate-x-1/2` for true geometric centering (center of viewport); these do not change with direction.

## Margin

| Physical | Logical |
| -------- | ------- |
| `ml-*` | `ms-*` |
| `mr-*` | `me-*` |

## Padding

| Physical | Logical |
| -------- | ------- |
| `pl-*` | `ps-*` |
| `pr-*` | `pe-*` |

## Borders and rounding

| Physical | Logical |
| -------- | ------- |
| `border-l-*` | `border-s-*` |
| `border-r-*` | `border-e-*` |
| `rounded-l-*` | `rounded-s-*` |
| `rounded-r-*` | `rounded-e-*` |

## Animations

Use logical slide utilities so motion follows text direction:

| Physical | Logical |
| -------- | ------- |
| `slide-in-from-left-*` | `slide-in-from-start-*` |
| `slide-in-from-right-*` | `slide-in-from-end-*` |
| `slide-out-to-left-*` | `slide-out-to-start-*` |
| `slide-out-to-right-*` | `slide-out-to-end-*` |

**Bad:**
```tsx
className="absolute top-2 right-2 ml-4 pl-2 data-[side=left]:slide-in-from-right-2"
```

**Good:**
```tsx
className="absolute top-2 end-2 ms-4 ps-2 data-[side=left]:slide-in-from-end-2"
```
